-- Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Candente, Panoro, Trevali
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-07-17T21:34:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-17/peru-stocks-buenaventura-candente-panoro-trevali.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of the close of trade in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 0.2 percent to 20,033.85. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid 0.1 percent to 2,695.12.  Trevali Mining Corp. (TV)  , a Canadian zinc and silver
producer with operations in Peru, dropped 4.8 percent to 80
cents after zinc declined in  London .  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian copper
exploration company, slumped 3.6 percent to 53 cents. Shares
fell after copper declined in  New York , said Estefany Castillo,
an analyst at Scotiabank Peru.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, decreased 1.6 percent to 63 cents.  Luna Gold Corp. (LGC)  , a Canadian gold explorer, slumped
6.3 percent to $1.92 after gold declined in New York.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the countryâ€™s
biggest precious-metals miner, slid 1.4 percent to $36.49.  To contact the reporter on this story:
